\#\#\# User: I have a problem with the subscript under the sum,

```
\sum_{i \in X} \sum_{i \in \bar{X}}

```

for example gives the subscript at different heights for each sum. Does anyone know how to fix this? 

 \-

\#\#\# Top Answer: This can be solved using the [`mathtools`](http://ctan.org/pkg/mathtools) package and its command `\adjustlimits`:

```
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{mathtools}
\begin{document}
\[
  \adjustlimits\sum_{i \in X}\sum_{i \in \bar{X}}
\]
\end{document}

```

